      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The core of healthy nationalism is the commitment to the well-being and self-determination of one's own people, which is a legitimate political goal. The dangerous element arises when that commitment morphs into an inherent belief in the superiority of one's group over all others, leading to hostility toward outsiders. A strong national identity is necessary for a society to have a shared purpose and defend its interests on the global stage. The distinction is between pride in one's culture and hatred of others.",
